<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - COMPONENT CHANGES
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>COMPONENT CHANGES</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>VIBRATION DAMPER</title>
            <para>Effective with S/N 532981, the crankshaft pulley/ vibration dampers installed on production engines
                have three belt grooves. This reduction of one groove is a result of the change to the gear driven
                steering pump. Current production DTA model engines will continue to use a viscous vibration damper.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>DO NOT MIX A RUBBER VIBRATION DAMPER AND PULLEY ASSEMBLY WITH A VISCOUS VIBRATION DAMPER AND
                        PULLEY ASSEMBLY. DO NOT MIX THREE AND FOUR GROOVE PULLEYS DUE TO THE DIFFERENT CENTER LINE OF
                        PULLEY GROOVES.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4150704" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11892" filename="../figcg1/CG11892.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.4. Crankshaft Pulley/Vibration Damper.</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
